<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-687-934  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 687 934.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  July 31 1990 v4 n26 p33(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Coastal Associates Publishing L.P. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Format translator Software Bridge crossing over to Mac. (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Norr, Henry.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Systems Compatibility Corp. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Software Bridge for the Macintosh (Data conversion software)(product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionFormatWord Processing SoftwareAdd-In-On SoftwareConversion.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   Word processing programs supported by Software Bridge Mac. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Henry NorrandM;Chicago -- Promising to bring some competition to what has long been aone-horse race, a leading developer of format-translation software for IBMPCs and compatibles and DEC VAXes this month announced its entry into the Macmarket with a new package of word processing format translators for use withthe Apple File Exchange utility.andM;Systems Compatibility Corp., a 10-year-old developer best known for itsSoftware Bridge package for MS-DOS platforms, said it would begin shippingSoftware Bridge Mac this week.andM;The $129 package provides 380 possible pairings among 24 popular wordprocessing formats on the Mac and PC.andP;  Each pairing has a complementary onethat works in the reverse direction, so any converted file can be restored toits original format.andP;  Users create a custom translator file with all desiredpairings.andP;  When a document and the translator file are selected in Apple FileExchange, Software Bridge Mac automatically identifies the file format; theuser does not even need to know the source file's format, the company said.andM;The format-translation category has been dominated by DataViz Inc., theTrumbull, Conn., publisher of the MacLink Plus series.andP;  But SystemsCompatibility said its program will support a number of formatting featuresthe DataViz product may not, including headers and footers, hard page breaks,side-by-side columns, and top and bottom margins.andP;  In addition, SystemsCompatibility said its program reliably retains graphics and fonts whentranslating between two Mac word processors.andM;Systems Compatibility Corp. is located at 401 N. Wabash, Suite 600, Chicago,Ill.andP;  60611; (312) 329-0700.andO;</TEXT></DOC>